main event: A white object, the size of a nickel with no distinct shape, was observed near Alpine, Arizona on November 13, 1957, moving downward at a steady pace for about 10 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as having no distinct shape and was the size of a nickel.
It was observed moving downward for a duration of 10 minutes, suggesting controlled movement.
An astro-camera showed Venus in the sky at the same time, but it did not pinpoint the exact direction of the observed object.
The observation was made by a civilian at a ranger station in Alpine, Arizona.
No photographs were taken during the sighting.
sighted object: white object, size of a nickel, no distinct shape
